# infravision-agent

**Linux / EC2 monitoring agent.** Install on any EC2 instance (or any Linux server), and it serves every system metric — CPU, RAM, disk, network, processes, Docker containers, and Falco security events — as a single live JSON payload on **one port**.

```
curl http://your-ec2:5010/
```

---

## Install

```bash
# From PyPI (after publishing)
pip install infravision-agent

# With Docker container stats
pip install "infravision-agent[docker]"

# From source
git clone https://github.com/your-org/infravision-agent
pip install ./infravision-agent
```

**Requirements:** Python 3.6+, Linux (any distro). `psutil`, `rich`, `click` are installed automatically.

---

## Quick start

```bash
# Start the metrics server on port 5010
infravision start

# In another terminal — pull all metrics
curl http://localhost:5010/

# Live stream (Server-Sent Events, pushes every 5 s)
curl -N http://localhost:5010/stream

# Terminal dashboard (like htop)
infravision dash

# One-shot status snapshot
infravision status
```

---

## HTTP API

All metrics come from **one port**. No sub-paths per metric — everything in one response.

| Endpoint | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `GET :5010/` | Complete live JSON snapshot — all sections |
| `GET :5010/stream` | Server-Sent Events — pushes fresh JSON every 5 s |
| `GET :5010/health` | Liveness probe |

### Query parameters

| Param | Default | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `pretty` | `1` | Pretty-print JSON (`0` for compact) |
| `interval` | `5` | SSE push interval in seconds (stream only) |

### Example response — `GET :5010/`

