---

## CLI reference

```bash
infravision start   [--port 5010] [--host 0.0.0.0] [--verbose]
infravision dash    [--refresh 2.0]
infravision status  [--section system|disk|processes|network|docker|security|all] [--json]
infravision check
infravision install   [--port 5010]      # requires root — installs systemd service
infravision uninstall                    # requires root
```

---

## Deploy to EC2

### Option A — pip (recommended)

```bash
# On EC2
pip3 install infravision-agent
sudo infravision install --port 5010
```

### Option B — install.sh (auto-installs Python + pip if needed)

```bash
scp install.sh ec2-user@<ec2-ip>:~
ssh ec2-user@<ec2-ip>
sudo bash install.sh --port 5010 --falco
```

### Option C — one-liner (after PyPI publish)

```bash
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/your-org/infravision-agent/main/install.sh | sudo bash
```

---

## Falco integration

```bash
# Run Falco alongside the agent
docker run -d --name falco --restart unless-stopped --privileged \
  -v /var/run/docker.sock:/host/var/run/docker.sock \
  -v /dev:/host/dev         -v /proc:/host/proc:ro \
  -v /boot:/host/boot:ro    -v /lib/modules:/host/lib/modules:ro \
  -v /usr:/host/usr:ro      -v /etc:/host/etc:ro \
  falcosecurity/falco:master-debian

# Falco events appear automatically in :5010/ under security.falco.recent_events
```

---

## Use as a Python library

```python
from infravision_agent.server import run_server_background
import time, urllib.request, json

# Start server in background thread
run_server_background(host="0.0.0.0", port=5010)
time.sleep(6)  # wait for first collection

# Pull all metrics
data = json.loads(urllib.request.urlopen("http://localhost:5010/").read())
print(data["system"]["cpu"]["usage_total"], "% CPU")
print(data["system"]["memory"]["percent"],  "% RAM")
print(len(data["docker"]["containers"]),    "containers")

# Use individual collectors directly
from infravision_agent.collectors import system, disk, docker_collector
print(system.collect_all())
print(disk.collect_all())
print(docker_collector.collect_all())
```

---

## Security group rule

**Important:** Restrict port 5010 to your monitoring server only.

```bash
aws ec2 authorize-security-group-ingress \
  --group-id sg-xxxxxxxxxx \
  --protocol tcp --port 5010 \
  --cidr <monitoring-server-ip>/32
```

