## Compatibility

| Distro | Status |
|--------|--------|
| Ubuntu 20.04 / 22.04 / 24.04 | ✅ |
| Debian 10 / 11 / 12 | ✅ |
| Amazon Linux 2 / 2023 | ✅ |
| CentOS 7 / Stream 8 / 9 | ✅ |
| RHEL 7 / 8 / 9 | ✅ |
| Fedora 38+ | ✅ |
| Arch Linux | ✅ |
| Alpine Linux | ✅ |
| Raspberry Pi OS | ✅ |

Python 3.6 — 3.12 supported. `psutil` required. `docker` optional.

---

## How to publish to PyPI

```bash
pip install build twine

cd infravision-agent
python -m build                          # creates dist/

twine check dist/*
twine upload dist/*                      # prompts for PyPI credentials
```

After publishing:
```bash
pip install infravision-agent
```

---

## Project structure

```
infravision-agent/
├── pyproject.toml
├── setup.py
├── MANIFEST.in
├── LICENSE
├── README.md
├── install.sh
└── infravision_agent/
    ├── __init__.py
    ├── __main__.py               python3 -m infravision_agent start
    ├── cli.py                    click CLI
    ├── server.py                 HTTP server on port 5010
    ├── collectors/
    │   ├── system.py             CPU / RAM / load / uptime
    │   ├── disk.py               df -h + partitions + I/O
    │   ├── processes.py          top processes (htop-style)
    │   ├── network.py            interfaces + connections
    │   ├── docker_collector.py   container stats
    │   └── security.py           Falco / SSH / fail2ban
    └── display/
        └── dashboard.py          Rich live TUI
```
